The paper deals with machine learning algorithms applied to predict agent behaviors in real-world dynamic systems. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of Markov Chain in Random Environments (MCRE) to describe the behavior data, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and stochastic processes (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization analysis of the machine learning algorithms, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
